  "body": "In k8s 1.4, we were able to set up a symlink from `/etc/kubernetes/manifests/etcd.manifest` to a mountpoint (`/mnt/etcd-volume/k8s.io/etcd.manifest`), to ensure that the pod could not be started before the volume was mounted.\r\n\r\nk8s 1.5 broke this: the inotify poller does not detect when the volume is mounted, because the inotify watch does not traverse symlinks: https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/kubelet/config/file_linux.go#L58\r\n\r\nAlso:\r\n\r\n* We probably should include `IN_ATTRIB` so that users can touch the file / symlink\r\n* We probably need to move to fsnotify, or create our own fork of inotify, because inotify has been deleted: https://github.com/golang/exp/tree/master/inotify  (It's 300 lines, mostly symbol definitions, we should probably bring it in to k8s)\r\n* I suggest we should probably have a time based poll in addition, to catch anything the inotify misses\r\n* It is unsafe to ignore IN_Q_OVERFLOW, I believe\r\n\r\ncc @dchen1107 ",
